<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-3-5-highjump-approx">
    <statement>
        <p>
            A high-jumper jumps so that the height, <m>H</m> feet, of the point on his back that must clear the bar after <m>T</m> seconds is given by the equation <me>H = 3.5 + 16T -16T^2</me>.
        </p>

        <figure xml:id="fig-3-5-act-high-jumper">
            <caption><m>H</m> = the height of the high jumper, as a function of <m>T</m>= time.</caption>
                <image>
                <shortdescription>Height of a high jumper vs. time</shortdescription>
                <prefigure xmlns="https://prefigure.org"
                    label="prefigure-act-high-jumper">
                    <xi:include href="../prefigure/3-5-high-jumper.xml" />
                </prefigure>
            </image>
        </figure>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use the graph above to find <em>approximately</em> when the high-jumper would hit the ground (if there were no pit).
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Use successive approximation to refine your guess.
                </p>
                <xi:include href="../successive-approx.ptx" />
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>